    "name": "Hotel Offer Orchestrator",
    "description": "Tests for the Express API (`src/app.ts`, `src/routes/hotelRoutes.ts`).\n\n**Prerequisites**\n- App on port 3000 (`npm run dev` or `npm start` after `npm run build`)\n- Redis reachable (used when persisting `/api/hotels` results)\n- Temporal worker running (`npm run worker`) so `/api/hotels` can execute the workflow\n\n**Optional: one supplier down**\nThe worker calls `SUPPLIER_BASE_URL` (default `http://localhost:3000`) for `/supplierA/hotels` and `/supplierB/hotels`. To simulate a failure:\n1. Run a mock HTTP server (e.g. Mockoon) that returns **503** (or non-JSON) for **only** `/supplierA/hotels` and returns a JSON **array** for `/supplierB/hotels`.\n2. Start the worker with `SUPPLIER_BASE_URL` pointing at that mock.\n3. Call **GET /health** — expect **503** and `suppliers.supplierA.ok: false`. **GET /api/hotels** will fail the workflow if either supplier fetch throws.\n\nCity matching is case-insensitive (`filterByCity`).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Hotels API",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /api/hotels — Delhi (overlaps)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/hotels?city=delhi",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "hotels"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "city",
                  "value": "delhi",
                  "description": "Both suppliers list Holtin; workflow dedupes by name and keeps lowest price (supplier B wins)."
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Expects 200 and a JSON array. **Holtin** appears once with the cheaper supplier B row (`hotelId` **b1**, price **5340**)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const hotels = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Body is array', () => pm.expect(Array.isArray(hotels)).to.be.true);",
                  "pm.test('Has offers for Delhi', () => pm.expect(hotels.length).to.be.at.least(1));",
                  "const holtin = hotels.filter((h) => h.name === 'Holtin');",
                  "pm.test('Holtin deduped to single row', () => pm.expect(holtin.length).to.eql(1));",
                  "pm.test('Holtin is lowest-price supplier (B)', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(holtin[0].hotelId).to.eql('b1');",
                  "  pm.expect(holtin[0].price).to.eql(5340);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/hotels — No results",
          "request": {
